<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Spinner" />
    <h3><code>ui:spinner</code></h3>
    <p><code>ui:spinner</code> is a loading indicator that is displayed while your component body is loading. 
    To toggle its visibility,  use <code>cmp.get("e.toggle")</code> and set the <code>isVisible</code> parameter to <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.
    The <code>ui:spinner</code> component fires the <code>toggle</code> event.
    </p>
    
    <auradocs:viewer descriptor="auradocs:demoSpinner" />
    <p>Note that <code>cmp.get("e.toggle")</code> is used to get the toggle event, while <code>isVisible</code> is a parameter on the <code>toggle</code> event. 
    Call <code>fire()</code> on the event to toggle the spinner, as shown by <code>evt.fire();</code> in the controller action. </p>
     <auradocs:info>See the <auradocs:defLink descriptor ="ui:spinner">ui:spinner</auradocs:defLink> component reference for more information.</auradocs:info>
    
</aura:component>